RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 3 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 78. Claiming Purse 7900. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND OLDER THAT HAVE STARTED AT THE 2023 RILLITO PARK MEET AND HAVE NOT FINISHED BETTER THAN THIRD. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $3,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HULA KING Pressed pace early along rail, moved up inside leader to challenge at the seven-sixteenths pole, continued fight on rail while traveling best, fended off challengers at the eighth and into the stretch, drew off handily. LIL LATIGO Forced four wide into the first turn, commenced a three wide move to the lead inside the three-eighths, continued to vie around turn, came home on the wrong lead, second best. TRACK BOUND Set into the five path around the first turn tracking the pace, moved four wide at the three-eighths to battle for the lead, remained four wide on the far turn, got out a few paths at the eighth pole, ran evenly through the stretch. BIGGER THAN YOU Broke awkwardly outwards, led two wide into the first turn, overtaken at the seven-sixteenths but remained in conention in a line of four, fought, faded from the sixteenth home. AMITY HARBOR Stalked three wide into the first turn, advanced at the three-eighths pole, just short of room between without anywhere to really progress further, chased top quartet from the quarter pole to the eighth pole, not a threat to winner. OUTLAW BY NATURE Settled off the pace on the rail, was never able to reach a challenging position. MIDNIGHT DRAMA Stumbled at the break, the rider lost the irons and never regained them throughout the event, settled in the two pace off the pace, made a mild move up the backside, had nothing left for the stretch run, departed with rider shortly after the wire, walked off. HAMMERING LEMON In rear throughout, wide on both turns and never factored. A RIDERS OBJECTION FROM #6 AMITY HARBOR WAS LODGED AGAINST #4 BIGGER THAN YOU. NO CHANGE WAS MADE.

ENTRY.NAME: Midnight Drama
ENTRY.COMMENT: Stumble, lost irons, 2p off pace, mild move, no left

ENTRY.NAME: Outlaw by Nature
ENTRY.COMMENT: Off pace rail, never in challenging position

ENTRY.NAME: Hula King
ENTRY.OWNER: Ortega, Jr., Alex and Ortega, Vincent
ENTRY.COMMENT: Rail press, move up 7/16, fend off challengers, drew off

ENTRY.NAME: Bigger Than You
ENTRY.COMMENT: Broke out, led 2w first, overtaken 7/16, fought, faded late

ENTRY.NAME: Hammering Lemon
ENTRY.COMMENT: In rear, wide turns, no factor

ENTRY.NAME: Amity Harbor
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3w first, adv. 3/8, short of room between, chased, no threat

ENTRY.NAME: Lil Latigo
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4w first, 3w move to lead, vied, wrong lead stretch, 2nd best

ENTRY.NAME: Track Bound
ENTRY.COMMENT: 5p tracking, move 4w 3/8ths, 4w turn, evenly stretch

EDINBURGH EXPRESS Dueled between early, left to hold hold and battle at the quarter pole, could not match the winner. DARKSABER Vied early while chasing top trio, bowed out from the four horse battle just outside the quarter pole, swung to the four path into the lane, came home evenly. SHELBY R. Broke best, vied three wide, backed out at the quarter pole, finished off with mild interest. NIGHTHAWK SPECIAL Tracked off the pace and off the rail, never a threat. BECOME AN INSIDER Ran detached in the back, never contended.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: TAINO HOUSE Stumbled at the start, let outer rival clear in run to first turn, switched to two path around that bend, advanced just inside the seven-sixteenths to a clear lead, put field away, won without any doubt. RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 6 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 88. Allowance Purse 10000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND OLDER. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MIKE OPERATOR Sent and led throughout, shifted out a path from rail positioning around the third and final turn, saw off all comers. CHEF Tracked along the rail, advanced inside at the three-eighths, tried to take advantage of hole at the eighth pole, staved off by the winner. STRAUS'S PLACE In the rear early along the rail, commenced at the quarter pole and picked up well, split rivals into the lane, just had too much to do. BIG CITY BANE Settled in back along the three path, dove inside of rivals at the three-eighths, made steady progression around the final bend, ran evenly through the lane. COURAGEOUS Pressed the leader and eventual winner from the outset in the two path, maintained position until dropping out at the quarter pole. BACK TO BUSINESS Set up in a pocket behind leader and presser into first turn, dropped back steadily in first run by the stands, shifted to the four path around second turn, emptied from there. BULLY RIDE Traveled off the pace two wide, gave way at the three-eighths, never a threat to anyone.

ENTRY.NAME: Back to Business
ENTRY.COMMENT: In pocket 1st, dropped back 1st time by, 4p 2nd, emptied

ENTRY.NAME: Chef
ENTRY.COMMENT: Track rail, adv 3/8 rail, threaten 1/8, staved off

ENTRY.NAME: Bully Ride
ENTRY.COMMENT: Off pace 2w, gave way 3/8, no threat

ENTRY.NAME: Mike Operator
ENTRY.COMMENT: Sent, led, shift 2p third, saw off all comers

ENTRY.NAME: Straus's Place
ENTRY.COMMENT: In rear rail, flew from 1/4 home, split rivals lane, toomuchtodo

ENTRY.NAME: Big City Bane
ENTRY.COMMENT: Back 3p, move 3/8 ins rivals, steady adv turn, evenly lane

ENTRY.NAME: Courageous
ENTRY.OWNER: Kling, Hedy and Hop, Michael D.
ENTRY.COMMENT: Press 2w, dropped out 1/4

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 7 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 84. Allowance Purse 9600. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND OLDER WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE SEPTEMBER 11, 2022. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MINISTERSDON'TLIE Hustled hard to the lead, settled up the backstretch, waved goodbye to the field at the quarter pole, trounced the competition. SAN GIORGIO Settled in behind runners early, moved three wide up the backside, fully commenced at the five-sixteenths and advanced widest of all, continued steady gain while being forced four wide through the lane, a clear second best in the wake of a no doubt winner. OMACHE KID Stalked in the four path into the first turn, traveled kindly in the two path up to the quarter pole when asked by rider, ran evenly through the stretch. TIGER BY HIS TAIL Tracked in behind top flight runners early, scrubbed at the five-sixteenths to present more feet, was no match to the top trio when the running got going. TIZ A SPEED BOMB Forced to press two wide when unable to outfoot MINISTERSDON'TLIE to the lead, tried to keep up with that rival but he shook clear, allowed to move to the rail and try to fight up to the three-sixteenths, gave way shortly after.

ENTRY.NAME: San Giorgio
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3w backside, adv 5/16 widest, steady gain, 2nd best

ENTRY.NAME: Ministersdon'tlie
ENTRY.COMMENT: Hustled hard, comfy backside run, opened up 1/4, trounced field

ENTRY.NAME: Tiger by His Tail
ENTRY.COMMENT: Tracked behind leaders, scrubbed 5/16, no match in running

ENTRY.NAME: Tiz a Speed Bomb
ENTRY.COMMENT: Press 2w, tried to keep up, rail 3/16, gave way

ENTRY.NAME: Omache Kid
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4p 1st stalking, ask 1/4 2p, evenly stretch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 8 6F Dirt CR: 72. Allowance Purse 9000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND OLDER WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HAYNESPUN Moved four wide in a line of five into the first turn, between rivals second flight in run up to the backstretch, advanced three wide at the three-eighths pole, continued steady gain to eighth pole, locked horns with leader at the sixteenth pole, kept finding to get up in dying stages. PRINCESS SUGEITH Maintained the rail into the first turn, led to the sixteenth pole when joined, fought on the inside of that rival, caught late. KIND BUT SHE LIES Forced five wide in a line of five into the first turn, had to stalk, advanced in the four path at the five-sixteenths pole, presented a mild gain, unable to match the top two. LILY PAD LAKE Settled three wide into the first turn, taken back slightly to stalk inside behind the top trio, commenced at the three-eighths along the rail, evenly down the stretch. ARCTIC FIRE Two wide into the first turn, briefly pressed the pace, dropped out at the five-sixteenths pole, taken care of in run to the wire.

ENTRY.NAME: Princess Sugeith
ENTRY.COMMENT: Rail 1st, led, fought inner stretch, caught

ENTRY.NAME: Arctic Fire
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2w 1st, briefly pressed pace, dropped out 5/16, taken care of

ENTRY.NAME: Lily Pad Lake
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3w 1st, stalk in behind top trio, rail 3/8, rail str, evenly

ENTRY.NAME: Haynespun
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4w 1st, btwn 7/16, adv 3w 3/8, steady gain to 1/8, kept finding

ENTRY.NAME: Kind But She Lies
ENTRY.COMMENT: 5w 1st, forced stalk, adv 4p 5/16, mild gain, unable to match
